            "text": "Automatic metrics are widely used in machine translation as a substitute for human assessment . <S>",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT-REASON"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "With the introduction of any new metric comes the question ",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 2,
            "text": "of just how well that metric mimics human assessment of translation quality . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 9,
            "text": "This is often measured by correlation with human judgment . <S>",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "Significance tests are generally not used ",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 5,
            "text": "to establish ",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "whether improvements over existing methods such as BLEU are statistically significant ",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "or have occurred simply by chance , however . <S>",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "In this paper , we introduce a significance test ",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 9,
            "text": "for comparing correlations of two metrics , along with an open-source implementation of the test . <S>",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "When applied to a range of metrics across seven language pairs , ",
            "relation": "CONDITION"
        },
        {
            "id": 12,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "tests show ",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        },
        {
            "id": 13,
